         <abstract>
            <p>This record refers to a collection of miracles of the Trinity transmitted together with
               <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1300Dersan">Dǝrsāna Śǝllāse</ref>, described in the following paragraphs.
               It is different from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2281Trinity">Taʾammǝra Śǝllāse</ref> (a collection of miracles of the Trinity attributed
               to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2748BeduaA">Bǝḍuʿa ʾAmlāk</persName>) and from
               <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2286ZenaSellase">Zenā nagaromu la-Śǝllāse</ref> (the collection of prayers to the Trinity
               <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2296Sayfas">Sayfa Śǝllāse</ref> arranged according
               to the days of the week with miracles of the Trinity).</p>
            <p>
               From     <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/CDVHURR9"><seg type="encyclopediaArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Nosnitsin2010EAETammeraS"/><title level="a">Täʾammǝrä sǝllase</title><title type="short">EAe</title><title level="m">Encyclopaedia Aethiopica</title><author><forename>Denis</forename><surname>Nosnitsin</surname></author><editor><forename>Siegbert</forename><surname>Uhlig</surname></editor><editor><forename>Alessandro</forename><surname>Bausi</surname></editor><pubPlace>Wiesbaden</pubPlace><publisher>Harrassowitz Verlag</publisher><date>2010</date><biblScope unit="volume">IV</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">975-976</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Nosnitsin2010EAETammeraS</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Nosnitsin2010EAETammeraS</note></bibl> (minimally rephrased):
            This set of miracles is part of the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1300Dersan">Dǝrsāna Śǝllāse</ref>. The miracles mostly conform to the pattern of
            <foreign xml:lang="gez">taʾammǝr</foreign>, telling of wonders worked by the Trinity both abroad (Egypt, Palestine etc., occasionally
            picking biblical stories) and in Ethiopia.</p>
            <p>This work is attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML150">Collegeville, Hill Museum and Manuscript Library, MS EMML no. 150</ref>, <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML1882">Collegeville, Hill Museum and Manuscript Library, MS EMML no. 1882</ref>
               and <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/SHOr409">Hamburg, State and University Library Hamburg Carl von Ossietzky, Cod. orient. 409</ref>.</p>
         </abstract>
